<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED38FFBAFF54FF20FE1CFEB4" pageId="42" pageNumber="193" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B534515BED38FFBAFF54FF20FE1CFEB4" blockId="42.[151,1436,150,323]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED38FFBAFF54FF20FEC0FF18" bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED38FFBAFD86FF21FD1EFF18" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[533,668,150,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="callainus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED38FFBAFD86FF21FD1EFF18" box="[533,668,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">C. callainus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED38FFBAFD30FF20FD7FFF18" bold="true" box="[675,765,150,176]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED38FFBAFD30FF20FD7FFF18" box="[675,765,150,176]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but can be distinguished by the presence of a tegular bump (TB, 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED38FFBAFF41FF0CFEB4FF7C" box="[210,310,186,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–233" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1383,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@44.[205,1383,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 228–233. Palp of Charippus yunnanensis (Cao &amp; Li, 2016) comb. nov., in prolateral (228), ventral (229), retrolateral (230), pro-ventral (231), retro-ventral (232) and dorsal (233) view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500864/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Figs 229</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED38FFBAFED2FF0CFE2AFF7D" box="[321,424,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 234–236" captionStartId="45.[151,264,1200,1224]" captionTargetBox="[152,1433,190,1175]" captionTargetId="figure-19@45.[151,1436,181,1175]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURES 234–236. Palp of Charippus yunnanensis (Cao &amp; Li, 2016) comb. nov., in pro-ventral (234), ventral (235) and retrolateral (236) view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500866/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">235–236</figureCitation>
), the absence of the serrulate-edged LED, and the salticid radix (SR) not obviously sclerotized in the male (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED38FFBAFEF0FF68FE4BFF50" box="[355,457,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–233" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1383,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@44.[205,1383,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 228–233. Palp of Charippus yunnanensis (Cao &amp; Li, 2016) comb. nov., in prolateral (228), ventral (229), retrolateral (230), pro-ventral (231), retro-ventral (232) and dorsal (233) view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500864/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Figs 229</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED38FFBAFE46FF68FD81FF51" box="[469,515,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 234–236" captionStartId="45.[151,264,1200,1224]" captionTargetBox="[152,1433,190,1175]" captionTargetId="figure-19@45.[151,1436,181,1175]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURES 234–236. Palp of Charippus yunnanensis (Cao &amp; Li, 2016) comb. nov., in pro-ventral (234), ventral (235) and retrolateral (236) view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500866/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">235</figureCitation>
), and by the absence of a wide sclerotized area above the epigynal window in the female (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED38FFBAFF61FEB4FE10FEB4" box="[242,402,258,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 237–244" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1453,1477]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,181,1417]" captionTargetId="figure-19@46.[155,1433,181,1429]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 237–244. Female genitalia of Charippus yunnanensis (Cao &amp; Li, 2016) comb. nov., in ventral (237, 239, 242) and dorsal (238, 240, 241, 243) view, CD path (244)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500868/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Figs 237–240</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED38FFBBFF54FE90FF5DFF7D" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="194" pageId="42" pageNumber="193" type="description">
<paragraph id="B534515BED38FFBAFF54FE90FD73FEE9" blockId="42.[151,1436,150,323]" box="[199,753,294,323]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED38FFBAFF54FE90FE21FEE8" bold="true" box="[199,419,294,320]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Description. Male.</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation id="D11A2CAAED38FFBAFE49FE90FD6EFEE9" author="Cao, Q. &amp; Li, S. Q. &amp; Zabka, M." box="[474,748,294,323]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193" pagination="43 - 104" refId="ref12943" refString="Cao, Q., Li, S. Q. &amp; Zabka, M. (2016) The jumping spiders from Xishuangbanna, Yunnan, China (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys, 630, 43 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 630.8466" type="journal article" year="2016">Cao, Li &amp; Żabka (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="E1F401D3ED38FFBAFF04F99EFE54F9CD" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500857" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6500857" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500857/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="193" startId="42.[151,264,1576,1600]" targetBox="[151,1436,344,1553]" targetPageId="42">
<paragraph id="B534515BED38FFBAFF04F99EFE54F9CD" blockId="42.[151,1436,1576,1637]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED38FFBAFF04F99EFEEDF9E8" bold="true" box="[151,367,1576,1600]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">FIGURES 214–220.</emphasis>
Living males of 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED38FFBAFDBBF99FFC59F9E9" authority="(Cao &amp; Li, 2016)" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Cao &amp; Li" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[552,987,1577,1601]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED38FFBAFDBBF99FFC9BF9E8" box="[552,793,1577,1601]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Charippus yunnanensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D11A2CAAED38FFBAFCB9F99FFC56F9E9" author="Cao, Q. &amp; Li, S. Q. &amp; Zabka, M." box="[810,980,1577,1601]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193" pagination="43 - 104" refId="ref12943" refString="Cao, Q., Li, S. Q. &amp; Zabka, M. (2016) The jumping spiders from Xishuangbanna, Yunnan, China (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys, 630, 43 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 630.8466" type="journal article" year="2016">Cao &amp; Li, 2016</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED38FFBAFC77F99FFBD9F9E9" bold="true" box="[996,1115,1577,1601]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED38FFBAFC77F99FFBD9F9E9" box="[996,1115,1577,1601]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(© Weihang Wang). 214–217, 219–220. Adult; 218. Subadult.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="B534515BED38FFBAFF54F925FECDF859" blockId="42.[151,1437,1683,2033]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED38FFBAFF54F925FEA7F905" bold="true" box="[199,293,1683,1709]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Female.</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED38FFBAFD80F925FD32F905" box="[531,688,1683,1709]" captionStart="FIGURES 221–227" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,561,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-175@43.[151,1436,561,1832]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 221–227. Charippus yunnanensis (Cao &amp; Li, 2016) comb. nov., male (221–222, 226) and female (223–225, 227). 221–224. Habitus, in dorsal (221, 223), lateral (222) and ventral (224) view; 225. Front view of carapace; 226. Sternum; 227. Details of left chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500859" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500859/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Figs 223–224</figureCitation>
. Carapace length 2.46 (variation: 2.41–2.46, n=2); abdomen length 2.32. Measurements of eyes: AME 0.47, ALE 0.32, PME 0.07, PLE 0.29. Measurements of legs: I 4.71 (1.46, 0.93, 1.14, 0.66, 0.52), II 3.87 (1.24, 0.72, 0.81, 0.67, 0.43), III 4.25 (1.41, 0.65, 0.82, 0.82, 0.55), IV 4.45 (1.43, 0.56, 0.95, 0.97, 0.54). Chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED38FFBAFE70F949FDC3F8B1" box="[483,577,1791,1817]" captionStart="FIGURES 221–227" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,561,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-175@43.[151,1436,561,1832]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 221–227. Charippus yunnanensis (Cao &amp; Li, 2016) comb. nov., male (221–222, 226) and female (223–225, 227). 221–224. Habitus, in dorsal (221, 223), lateral (222) and ventral (224) view; 225. Front view of carapace; 226. Sternum; 227. Details of left chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500859" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500859/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Fig. 227</figureCitation>
) dark brown, promargin with two teeth, retromargin with one bicuspid tooth. Sternum with setal tuft centrally. Dorsal abdomen not sclerotized. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED38FFBAFBC3F895FB70F895" box="[1104,1266,1827,1853]" captionStart="FIGURES 221–227" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,561,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-175@43.[151,1436,561,1832]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 221–227. Charippus yunnanensis (Cao &amp; Li, 2016) comb. nov., male (221–222, 226) and female (223–225, 227). 221–224. Habitus, in dorsal (221, 223), lateral (222) and ventral (224) view; 225. Front view of carapace; 226. Sternum; 227. Details of left chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500859" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500859/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Figs 223–224</figureCitation>
): carapace reddish brown, with two longitudinal dark bands between ALE and PLE; abdomen yellowish brown, without obvious markings. Epigynum (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED38FFBAFE04F8DDFDFAF82D" box="[407,632,1899,1925]" captionStart="FIGURES 237–244" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1453,1477]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,181,1417]" captionTargetId="figure-19@46.[155,1433,181,1429]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 237–244. Female genitalia of Charippus yunnanensis (Cao &amp; Li, 2016) comb. nov., in ventral (237, 239, 242) and dorsal (238, 240, 241, 243) view, CD path (244)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500868/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Figs 237, 239, 242</figureCitation>
): window large, with sclerotized rims, median septum narrow; lateral depressions shallow. Vulva (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED38FFBAFE48F839FD72F801" box="[475,752,1935,1961]" captionStart="FIGURES 237–244" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1453,1477]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,181,1417]" captionTargetId="figure-19@46.[155,1433,181,1429]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 237–244. Female genitalia of Charippus yunnanensis (Cao &amp; Li, 2016) comb. nov., in ventral (237, 239, 242) and dorsal (238, 240, 241, 243) view, CD path (244)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500868/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Figs 238, 240–241, 243</figureCitation>
): CD thin, swerving for seven times, with one small nodule between CO and AG; AG chilli-like, pointing dorsally (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED38FFBAFC87F805FCF7F865" box="[788,885,1971,1997]" captionStart="FIGURES 237–244" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1453,1477]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,181,1417]" captionTargetId="figure-19@46.[155,1433,181,1429]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 237–244. Female genitalia of Charippus yunnanensis (Cao &amp; Li, 2016) comb. nov., in ventral (237, 239, 242) and dorsal (238, 240, 241, 243) view, CD path (244)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500868/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Fig. 241</figureCitation>
) or laterally (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED38FFBAFB80F805FBF5F865" box="[1043,1143,1971,1997]" captionStart="FIGURES 237–244" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1453,1477]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,181,1417]" captionTargetId="figure-19@46.[155,1433,181,1429]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 237–244. Female genitalia of Charippus yunnanensis (Cao &amp; Li, 2016) comb. nov., in ventral (237, 239, 242) and dorsal (238, 240, 241, 243) view, CD path (244)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500868/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Fig. 240</figureCitation>
); spermathecae small and slightly bulging.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B534515BED39FFBBFF54FF21FF5DFF7D" blockId="43.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="43" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED39FFBBFF54FF21FE04FF18" bold="true" box="[199,390,150,177]" pageId="43" pageNumber="194">Natural history.</emphasis>
All specimens from XTBG were collected on the handrails of a footpath in the tropical rainforest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED39FFBBFF54FF69FCE4FE5D" pageId="43" pageNumber="194" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B534515BED39FFBBFF54FF69FCE4FE5D" blockId="43.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="43" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED39FFBBFF54FF69FEB9FF51" bold="true" box="[199,315,223,249]" pageId="43" pageNumber="194">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED39FFBBFED8FF69FDB7FF50" authorityName="Cao &amp; Li" authorityYear="2016" box="[331,565,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Cytaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="43" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED39FFBBFED8FF69FDB7FF50" box="[331,565,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="194">Cytaea yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from Menglun Nature Reserve (
<geoCoordinate id="D0BF379CED39FFBBFA94FF68FA1AFF51" box="[1287,1432,222,249]" degrees="21" direction="north" minutes="57.669" orientation="latitude" pageId="43" pageNumber="194" precision="1" value="21.96115">21°57.669'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="D0BF379CED39FFBBFF04FEB5FEB3FEB5" box="[151,305,259,285]" degrees="101" direction="east" minutes="11.893" orientation="longitude" pageId="43" pageNumber="194" precision="1" value="101.19822">101°11.893'E</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity id="7273FCBEED39FFBBFEAEFEB5FE06FEB5" box="[317,388,259,285]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.9" pageId="43" pageNumber="194" unit="m" value="790.0">790 m</quantity>
elev.), Xishuangbanna, based on the male 
<typeStatus id="6A30EFF9ED39FFBBFCF1FEB5FC46FEB5" box="[866,964,259,285]" pageId="43" pageNumber="194">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D11A2CAAED39FFBBFC40FEB5FB07FEB6" author="Cao, Q. &amp; Li, S. Q. &amp; Zabka, M." box="[979,1157,259,286]" pageId="43" pageNumber="194" pagination="43 - 104" refId="ref12943" refString="Cao, Q., Li, S. Q. &amp; Zabka, M. (2016) The jumping spiders from Xishuangbanna, Yunnan, China (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys, 630, 43 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 630.8466" type="journal article" year="2016">
Cao 
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED39FFBBFB9AFEB5FBC3FEB5" box="[1033,1089,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="194">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). We have collected both sexes of this species near the type locality. Some morphological evidence, such as the presence of a uniform tegular hump and a spine on the prolateral cymbium of male palp, the similar morphology of female genitalia and body form, the sexual dimorphism of setal tuft on the sternum, clearly show that 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED39FFBBFC60FED9FB57FE20" authorityName="Cao &amp; Li" authorityYear="2016" box="[1011,1237,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Cytaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="43" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED39FFBBFC60FED9FB57FE20" box="[1011,1237,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="194">Cytaea yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED39FFBBFF27FE25FE1BFE05" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[180,409,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="43" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="callainus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED39FFBBFF27FE25FE1BFE05" box="[180,409,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="194">Charippus callainus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED39FFBBFE33FE25FE78FE05" bold="true" box="[416,506,403,429]" pageId="43" pageNumber="194">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED39FFBBFE33FE25FE78FE05" box="[416,506,403,429]" pageId="43" pageNumber="194" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
. The morphological characters of these two species, such as the presence of CPSB and dense pits on the cephalon, and the lateral depressions on the epigynum, show that they belong to 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED39FFBBFA8CFE01FA17FE79" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1895" box="[1311,1429,439,465]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="43" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED39FFBBFA8CFE01FA17FE79" box="[1311,1429,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="194">Charippus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, we herein transfer 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED39FFBBFE76FE6DFD47FE5C" authorityName="Cao &amp; Li" authorityYear="2016" box="[485,709,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Cytaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="43" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
